Manufacturing Chemical Process Engineer

Pyrolyx USA Indiana, LLC

- Vigo County, IN

Job Summary:
The Manufacturing Process Engineer will create, develop, and implement efficient and safe process manufacturing systems, reducing costs while maintaining exceptional standards of operations. The Engineer will coordinate and manage production and technical development projects in an advanced manufacturing environment.
Duties/Responsibilities:
· Facilitates and contributes to the design and development of advanced technology manufacturing plants.
· Analyzes current engineering solutions and offers improvement ideas for design, process and quality.
· Ensures compliance with codes, guidelines, best practices, and company policies.
· Implements methods and modifications to reduce production costs and increase safety.
· Maintains knowledge of best practices in manufacturing methods, and trends and developments in technology and equipment; applies this knowledge to maintain the organizations competitive edge.
· Recommends and/or analyzes materials, equipment, and practices used in the project.
· Collaborates with the operations department to identify and troubleshoot problems.
· Supervises progress of production development projects.
· Performs other related duties as assigned.
Required Skills/Abilities:
· Excellent verbal and written communication skills.
· Thorough understanding of ergonomics and applicable industry standards.
· Excellent organizational skills and attention to detail.
· Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
· Proficient with Microsoft Office Suite or related software.
Supervisory Responsibilities:
· Cooperates with and assists with supervision of plant technicians.
Education and Experience:
· Bachelors degree in Mechanical (BSME), Electrical (BSEE), or Industrial Engineering required.
· Masters Degree preferred.
· At least 10 years of relevant experience, with 5-7 years of industrial engineering experience required.
· Chemical industry preferred.
Pyrolyx USA Indiana LLC offers a very competitive benefits package including medical, dental, and vision plans, group and voluntary term life insurance, short and long term disability coverage, and 401(k) retirement plan with company matching funds.
Job Type: Full-time
